Area police boss Kivinda Kilonzo said the accident occurred after the vehicle ran out of fuel. [Muriithi Mugo, Standard]  Several people are feared dead after a 21-seater mini-bus on Tuesday morning rolled down Thura River bridge in Kamugu Village, Mbeere North in Embu County.  Area police boss Kivinda Kilonzo said the accident occurred after the vehicle ran out of fuel while climbing the steep bridge.  “The driver sent the conductor to buy fuel from a nearby filling station. Upon returning with the fuel and igniting the engine, the vehicle rolled back and plunged into the river. We suspect several passengers died in the accident,” said Kilonzo.  The mini-bus, which belongs to KETNNO Sacco, was headed to Siakago Town from Gangara area.  Four killed, 12 injured in Narok accident  Land dispute: Murang’a family to cremate parents, sister   Film set accidents that have raised safety calls  MP Nassir staff killed in road accident Police suspect the vehicle was overloaded during the accident.   Gilgil Accident: PSV van crashes head on with a trailer, 9 reported dead with several others injured  Accident involving a matatu and a trailer claims eight lives along the Nairobi-Nakuru highway  4 people died in a road accident after personal car collided with a lorry along Machakos-Kitui road By Phares Mutembei | 4 days ago By Muriithi Mugo | 5 days ago By Muriithi Mugo | 5 days ago By Collins Kweyu | 6 days ago